{
  "texts": [
    "Unimodal Performance Analysis 1) Visual-Only Models: Table II summarizes image-only model performance.",
    "ResNet50 achieved the best accuracy of 66.85%, outperforming DenseNet169 (65.47%) and ResNet101 (64.32%).",
    "Figure 3 shows that visual models effectively separate distinct classes like Non Damage (ND) and Floods (FL), but struggle with ambiguous ones like Fires (FR) and Economic Loss (EL).TABLE II: Performance of Image-Only Models Model Acc.",
    "Recall F1 ResNet50 66.85 66.62 67.08 66.85 DenseNet169 65.47 65.23 65.71 65.47 ResNet101 64.32 64.15 64.49 64.32 MobileNetV2 62.41 62.17 62.65 62.41 2) Text-Only Models: Text-only models performed significantly better than visual models as shown in Table III.",
    "XLM-RoBERTa demonstrates superior multilingual support for Bangla text with 79.92% accuracy."
  ]
}